<subSubSection lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="296" pageId="1" pageNumber="290" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[828,1437,1496,2064]" pageId="1" pageNumber="290">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[828,944,1496,1520]" pageId="1" pageNumber="290">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Pronotum with posterior stripe, smoky brown to black, with black punctures, sometimes punctures on small dark spots (
<figureCitation box="[1033,1180,1561,1584]" captionStart="Figs 5" captionStartId="6.[151,188,2034,2053]" captionTargetBox="[248,1334,197,1986]" captionTargetId="figure-13@6.[179,1408,189,1996]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs 5A–F.Dorsal and ventral surface.A–B – Hypoxys servillei sp. nov.; C–D – Hypoxys stysi sp. nov.; E–F – Hypoxys venustus sp. nov. Scale bars = 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177537" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177537/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="290">Figs 5A,C,E</figureCitation>
); posterolateral angles somewhat prominent, smaller than eye width (
<figureCitation box="[1336,1423,1593,1616]" captionStart="Figs 1" captionStartId="2.[151,188,2036,2055]" captionTargetBox="[239,1341,201,1954]" captionTargetId="figure-13@2.[179,1408,189,1996]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1A–F. Dorsal and ventral surface. A–B – Hypoxys amyoti sp. nov.; C–D – Hypoxys aspilogaster sp. nov.; E–F – Hypoxys belenensis sp. nov. Scale bars = 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177529" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177529/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="290">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
). Anterolateral margin of pronotum yellow. Anterior half of scutellum with large, sparse punctures on dark spots (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figs 3" captionStartId="4.[151,188,2038,2057]" captionTargetBox="[242,1332,205,1992]" captionTargetId="figure-13@4.[179,1408,189,1996]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 3A–F. Dorsal and ventral surface. A–B – Hypoxys favachae sp. nov.; C–D – Hypoxys gaucho sp. nov.; E–F – Hypoxys hyalinofasciatus sp. nov. Scale bars = 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177533" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177533/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="290">Figs 3A,C,E</figureCitation>
). Connexivum uniformly green, without dark spots (
<figureCitation box="[835,946,1721,1744]" captionStart="Figs 5" captionStartId="6.[151,188,2034,2053]" captionTargetBox="[248,1334,197,1986]" captionTargetId="figure-13@6.[179,1408,189,1996]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs 5A–F.Dorsal and ventral surface.A–B – Hypoxys servillei sp. nov.; C–D – Hypoxys stysi sp. nov.; E–F – Hypoxys venustus sp. nov. Scale bars = 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177537" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177537/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="290">Figs 5A,E</figureCitation>
), except for 
<taxonomicName authority="Mendonca &amp; Nunes &amp; Fernandes, 2021" authorityName="Mendonca &amp; Nunes &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2021" box="[1073,1277,1721,1744]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigroantennatus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1073,1277,1721,1744]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="290">H. nigroantennatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1282,1363,1721,1744]" pageId="1" pageNumber="290" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Mendonca &amp; Nunes &amp; Fernandes, 2021" authorityName="Mendonca &amp; Nunes &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bergrothi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="290">H. bergrothi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[933,1015,1753,1776]" pageId="1" pageNumber="290" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
Body ventrally green, yellow medially, sometimes with narrow yellow transverse stripes; brown to black round spots on thorax (meso- and metapleura) and pseudosutures (
<figureCitation box="[1033,1143,1849,1872]" captionStart="Figs 5" captionStartId="6.[151,188,2034,2053]" captionTargetBox="[248,1334,197,1986]" captionTargetId="figure-13@6.[179,1408,189,1996]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs 5A–F.Dorsal and ventral surface.A–B – Hypoxys servillei sp. nov.; C–D – Hypoxys stysi sp. nov.; E–F – Hypoxys venustus sp. nov. Scale bars = 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177537" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177537/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="290">Figs 5B,D</figureCitation>
), except for 
<taxonomicName authority="Mendonca &amp; Nunes &amp; Fernandes, 2021" authorityName="Mendonca &amp; Nunes &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2021" box="[1270,1436,1849,1872]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="immaculatus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1270,1436,1849,1872]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="290">H. immaculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[828,911,1881,1904]" pageId="1" pageNumber="290" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<figureCitation box="[925,1008,1881,1904]" captionStart="Figs 4" captionStartId="5.[150,187,2036,2055]" captionTargetBox="[247,1334,221,1972]" captionTargetId="figure-16@5.[179,1408,189,1996]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 4A–F. Dorsal and ventral surface.A–B – Hypoxys immaculatus sp. nov.; C–D – Hypoxys nigroantennatus sp. nov.; E–F – Hypoxys santarensis sp. nov. Scale bars = 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177535" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177535/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="290">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName authority="Mendonca &amp; Nunes &amp; Fernandes, 2021" authorityName="Mendonca &amp; Nunes &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2021" box="[1069,1234,1881,1904]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aspilogaster" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1069,1234,1881,1904]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="290">H. aspilogaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1241,1325,1881,1904]" pageId="1" pageNumber="290" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<figureCitation box="[1339,1422,1881,1904]" captionStart="Figs 1" captionStartId="2.[151,188,2036,2055]" captionTargetBox="[239,1341,201,1954]" captionTargetId="figure-13@2.[179,1408,189,1996]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1A–F. Dorsal and ventral surface. A–B – Hypoxys amyoti sp. nov.; C–D – Hypoxys aspilogaster sp. nov.; E–F – Hypoxys belenensis sp. nov. Scale bars = 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177529" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177529/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="290">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
). Parameres almost straight in dorsal view, but never strongly curved laterally like in other species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Amyot &amp; Serville" authorityYear="1843" box="[1249,1341,1945,1968]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1249,1341,1945,1968]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="290">Hypoxys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1355,1436,1945,1968]" captionStart="Figs 7" captionStartId="10.[151,188,2010,2029]" captionTargetBox="[187,1400,195,1960]" captionTargetId="figure-13@10.[187,1401,189,1973]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs 7A–F. Hypoxys aspilogaster sp. nov. A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – genital plates; F – metasternal process. Green line in Fig. A indicates that paramere is straight. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177541" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177541/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="290">Fig. 7A</figureCitation>
– green dash). Ventral rim of pygophore with expansions (
<figureCitation box="[836,920,2009,2032]" captionStart="Figs 6" captionStartId="9.[150,187,2010,2029]" captionTargetBox="[188,1400,201,1947]" captionTargetId="figure-16@9.[187,1401,189,1973]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 6A–F.Hypoxys amyoti sp. nov.A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – genital plates; F – metasternal process. Abbteviations: dr – dorsal rim; gp – superior process of the genital cup; lat 8 – laterotergites 8; lat 9 – laterotergites 9; pa – parameres; proc – proctiger; vf 8 – valvifers 8; vf 9 – valvifers 9; vr – ventral rim; vre – ventral rim expansions; x – tenth segment. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177539" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177539/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="290">Fig. 6B</figureCitation>
) developed, acuminate, and triangular in cross section (
<figureCitation box="[922,1061,2041,2064]" captionStart="Figs 16" captionStartId="21.[151,188,2036,2055]" captionTargetBox="[176,1411,203,1987]" captionTargetId="figure-16@21.[175,1411,189,2007]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Figs 16A–F. Hypoxys nigroantennatus sp. nov. A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – genital plates; F – metasternal process. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177557" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177557/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="290">Figs 16B–D</figureCitation>
); expansions shallowly excavated
</paragraph>
