<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="296" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,760,190,917]" pageId="7" pageNumber="296">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,323,317,341]" pageId="7" pageNumber="296">Redescription.</emphasis>
Head. Mandibular plates and clypeus without black marks (except 
<taxonomicName authority="Mendonca &amp; Nunes &amp; Fernandes, 2021" authorityName="Mendonca &amp; Nunes &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2021" box="[454,659,350,373]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="296" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigroantennatus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[454,659,350,373]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="296">H. nigroantennatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[664,748,350,373]" pageId="7" pageNumber="296" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
). Thorax. Cicatrices of pronotum smooth. Scutellum with rare, minute punctures apically, some species have spots that resemble punctuation (
<figureCitation box="[444,531,446,469]" captionStart="Figs 1" captionStartId="2.[151,188,2036,2055]" captionTargetBox="[239,1341,201,1954]" captionTargetId="figure-13@2.[179,1408,189,1996]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1A–F. Dorsal and ventral surface. A–B – Hypoxys amyoti sp. nov.; C–D – Hypoxys aspilogaster sp. nov.; E–F – Hypoxys belenensis sp. nov. Scale bars = 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177529" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177529/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="296">Figs 1C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[544,580,446,469]" captionStart="Figs 2" captionStartId="3.[151,188,2034,2053]" captionTargetBox="[235,1334,206,1974]" captionTargetId="figure-16@3.[179,1408,189,1996]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 2A–F. Dorsal and ventral surface.A–B – Hypoxys bergrothi sp. nov.; C–D – Hypoxys breddini sp. nov.; E–F – Hypoxys caquetensis sp. nov. Scale bars = 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177531" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177531/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="296">2A</figureCitation>
). Evaporatorium and ventral surface of thorax concolorous.Abdomen. Connexivum with shallow punctures, punctures concolorous with abdomen. Distal half or less of segment VII black. Without dark transversal stripes ventrally. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[601,759,573,597]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="296">Male genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[159,282,606,629]" captionStart="Figs 6" captionStartId="9.[150,187,2010,2029]" captionTargetBox="[188,1400,201,1947]" captionTargetId="figure-16@9.[187,1401,189,1973]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 6A–F.Hypoxys amyoti sp. nov.A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – genital plates; F – metasternal process. Abbteviations: dr – dorsal rim; gp – superior process of the genital cup; lat 8 – laterotergites 8; lat 9 – laterotergites 9; pa – parameres; proc – proctiger; vf 8 – valvifers 8; vf 9 – valvifers 9; vr – ventral rim; vre – ventral rim expansions; x – tenth segment. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177539" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177539/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="296">Figs 6A–D</figureCitation>
). Bottom of ventral rim excavation with tiny fold. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[207,393,637,661]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="296">Female genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[408,491,638,661]" captionStart="Figs 6" captionStartId="9.[150,187,2010,2029]" captionTargetBox="[188,1400,201,1947]" captionTargetId="figure-16@9.[187,1401,189,1973]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 6A–F.Hypoxys amyoti sp. nov.A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – genital plates; F – metasternal process. Abbteviations: dr – dorsal rim; gp – superior process of the genital cup; lat 8 – laterotergites 8; lat 9 – laterotergites 9; pa – parameres; proc – proctiger; vf 8 – valvifers 8; vf 9 – valvifers 9; vr – ventral rim; vre – ventral rim expansions; x – tenth segment. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177539" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177539/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="296">Fig. 6E</figureCitation>
). Distal margin of laterotergites 8 and 9 black.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
